st be enabled in order to      allow user to claim pending reward"},"ROLE_DATA_ROOT_MANAGER":{"details":"Role ROLE_DATA_ROOT_MANAGER allows setting the Merkle tree root via setInputDataRoot()"}},"title":"Leaderboard Reward System","version":1},"userdoc":{"kind":"user","methods":{"FEATURE_CLAIM_ACTIVE()":{"notice":"Enables the airdrop, redeeming the tokens"},"ROLE_ACCESS_MANAGER()":{"notice":"Access manager is responsible for assigning the roles to users,      enabling/disabling global features of the smart contractAccess manager can add, remove and update user roles,      remove and update global features"},"ROLE_DATA_ROOT_MANAGER()":{"notice":"Data Root manager is responsible for supplying the valid input data array      Merkle root which then can be used to check total reward won by user."},"ROLE_UPGRADE_MANAGER()":{"notice":"Upgrade manager is responsible for smart contract upgrades,      see https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/4.x/api/proxy#UUPSUpgradeable      see https://docs.openzeppelin.com/contracts/4.x/upgradeable"},"claimReward(address,uint256,bytes32[])":{"notice":"total amount of token `_totalReward` to an address `_to`, verifying the validity      of a `(_to, _totalReward)` pair via the Merkle proof `_proof`"},"features()":{"notice":"Retrieves globally set of features enabled"},"getImplementation()":{"notice":"Returns an address of the implementation smart contract,      see ERC1967Upgrade._getImplementation()"},"getRole(address)":{"notice":"Reads the permissions (role) for a given user from the `userRoles` mapping      (privileged addresses with defined roles/permissions)In the context of ERC20/ERC721 tokens these can be permissions to      allow minting or burning tokens, transferring on behalf and so on"},"isClaimValid(address,uint256,bytes32[])":{"notice":"Verifies the validity of a `(_to, _totalReward)` pair supplied based on the Merkle root      of the entire `(_to, _totalReward)` data array (pre-stored in the contract), and the Merkle      p